## 5. LangGraph.js Streaming API

### Two Primary Methods

#### `graph.stream()` — Lower-level, direct chunk access
```typescript
for await (const chunk of await graph.stream(inputs, {
  streamMode: "updates",  // or "values" | "messages" | "custom" | "debug"
})) {
  // chunk shape depends on mode
  console.log(chunk);
}
```

| `streamMode` | What it yields | Best for |
|---|---|---|
| `"values"` | Full state snapshot after each step | Debugging, state inspection |
| `"updates"` | Only state deltas after each node | Dashboards, progress UI |
| `"messages"` | LLM tokens + metadata as generated | Chat "typing" effect |
| `"custom"` | Custom data emitted via writer | App-specific progress events |
| `"debug"` | Everything | Deep tracing |

#### `graph.streamEvents()` — Higher-level, event-based (recommended)

**v2 (current stable)**:
```typescript
const stream = graph.streamEvents(inputs, { version: "v2" });

for await (const event of stream) {
  const { event: eventType, data, metadata, name } = event;

  // Filter by event type
  if (eventType === "on_chat_model_stream") {
    // Filter by node
    if (metadata?.langgraph_node === "researchNode") {
      const token = data?.chunk?.content;
      if (token) process.stdout.write(token);
    }
  }
}
```

**v3 (experimental, recommended for new apps)**:
```typescript
const stream = await graph.streamEvents(inputs, { version: "v3" });

// Typed projections — cleaner API
for await (const message of stream.messages) {
  for await (const token of message.text) {
    process.stdout.write(token);
  }
}
const finalOutput = await stream.output;
```

### Event Types (v2)

| Event Type | When fired |
|---|---|
| `on_chain_start` | Node/chain starts |
| `on_chain_end` | Node/chain completes |
| `on_chat_model_start` | LLM call starts |
| `on_chat_model_stream` | Each LLM token |
| `on_chat_model_end` | LLM call completes |
| `on_tool_start` | Tool invoked |
| `on_tool_end` | Tool returns |

### Filtering by Node Name
```typescript
// Option 1: metadata field
if (metadata?.langgraph_node === "myNode") { ... }

// Option 2: includeNames config (v2)
const stream = graph.streamEvents(inputs,
  { version: "v2" },
  { includeNames: ["myNode", "anotherNode"] }  // 3rd arg filter options
);
```

